After you left that night,

00:39:52.100 --> 00:39:53.180
I realized something.

00:39:54.620 --> 00:39:56.460
We can be anything to each other.

00:39:59.860 --> 00:40:01.220
Just not lovers.

00:40:01.980 --> 00:40:02.820
Why?

00:40:04.060 --> 00:40:04.900
Don't get me wrong.

00:40:04.900 --> 00:40:05.780
I'm just curious.

00:40:08.220 --> 00:40:09.340
Let me tell you a story.

00:40:12.260 --> 00:40:13.500
Once there was a boy.

00:40:13.740 --> 00:40:16.380
He was drawn to a girl's portrait at a show.

00:40:16.660 --> 00:40:17.740
She was breathtaking.

00:40:18.180 --> 00:40:20.540
The boy bought it without a second thought.

00:40:26.420 --> 00:40:27.740
But when he got home, he realized

00:40:27.740 --> 00:40:29.380
he hadn't bought a painting at all,

00:40:29.700 --> 00:40:32.660
but thousands of puzzle pieces in a box.

00:40:33.500 --> 00:40:35.380
The boy missed the girl so much,

00:40:35.540 --> 00:40:36.860
so he started piecing it together.

00:40:37.540 --> 00:40:39.780
But the more he pieced, the stranger it felt.

00:40:40.540 --> 00:40:42.660
The girl's eyes no longer looked pure,

00:40:43.220 --> 00:40:45.260
but carried a sharp, angry glare.

00:40:45.740 --> 00:40:47.060
